#include &lt;google/protobuf/compiler/plugin.h&gt;
namespace google::protobuf::compiler
Front-end for protoc code generator plugins written in C++. To implement a protoc plugin in C++, simply write an implementation of CodeGenerator, then create a main() function like: int main(int argc, char* argv[]) { MyCodeGenerator generator; return google::protobuf::compiler::PluginMain(argc, argv, &amp;generator); } You must link your plugin against libprotobuf and libprotoc.
The core part of PluginMain is to invoke the given CodeGenerator on a CodeGeneratorRequest to generate a CodeGeneratorResponse.

